<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,380,656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,214,380,405]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Note.</emphasis>
Since knowledge on epigynal patterns in 
<taxonomicName box="[690,788,381,404]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[690,788,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Hypaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was limited to that described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano" box="[1167,1340,380,405]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1968) Revision de los generos Acragas, Amycus, Encolpius, Hypaeus, Mago y Noegus (Salticidae, Araneae). Revista del Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia (Ent.), 2, 267 - 360." type="journal article" year="1968">
Galiano (
<number box="[1272,1332,380,405]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="1968.0">1968</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2008) Redescription and resolution of some Neotropical species of jumping spiders described by Caporiacco and description of a new species (Araneae: Salticidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 25, 487 - 494. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752008000300013" type="journal article" year="2008">
Ruiz &amp; Brescovit (
<number box="[278,337,416,440]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
tentatively transferred 
<taxonomicName authority="Caporiacco" authorityName="Caporiacco" box="[620,1017,415,440]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Asaracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauciaculeis">
<emphasis box="[620,878,415,440]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Asaracus pauciaculeis</emphasis>
Caporiacco
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[1063,1128,417,440]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Mago" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1063,1128,417,440]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Mago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The similarities with the herein described females of 
<taxonomicName box="[483,642,452,477]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridactylus">
<emphasis box="[483,642,452,477]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. tridactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[704,843,452,477]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon">
<emphasis box="[704,843,452,477]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
allow a more accurate position for this species in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,249,489,512]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,249,489,512]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Hypaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,380,656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,524,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[460,636,524,549]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Asaracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauciaculeis">
<emphasis box="[460,636,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. pauciaculeis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[896,1051,524,549]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridactylus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[896,1051,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. tridactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1058,1148,524,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1058,1148,524,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1338,524,549]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1203,1338,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,524,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,524,549]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having the double pocket (female of 
<taxonomicName box="[607,747,559,584]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulifer">
<emphasis box="[607,747,559,584]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. annulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is still unknown). However, they can be distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[248,402,596,621]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridactylus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[248,402,596,621]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. tridactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[409,499,596,621]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[409,499,596,621]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
for the posterior position of the pockets and from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1299,596,621]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Hypaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poseidon" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1163,1299,596,621]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">H. poseidon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1306,1396,596,621]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1306,1396,596,621]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
for having wider pockets (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz" box="[449,712,631,656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" refString="Ruiz, G. R. S. &amp; Brescovit, A. D. (2008) Redescription and resolution of some Neotropical species of jumping spiders described by Caporiacco and description of a new species (Araneae: Salticidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 25, 487 - 494. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752008000300013" type="journal article" year="2008">
Ruiz &amp; Brescovit 
<number box="[652,712,632,656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[723,768,632,656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="488.0">488</number>
, figs 
<number box="[828,874,631,656]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6</number>
). Males are still unknown.
</paragraph>
